    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "Return the name of the user owning the file. KeyError is raised if the file’s user identifier (UID) isn’t found in the system database. This method normally follows symlinks; to get the owner of the symlink, add the argument follow_symlinks=False. Changed in version 3.13: Raises UnsupportedOperation if the pwd module is not available. In earlier versions, NotImplementedError was raised. Changed in version 3.13: The follow_symlinks parameter was added."
